Portuguese

[edit]

Pronunciation

[edit]
 
  • (Brazil) IPA(key): /pɾe.va.leˈse(ʁ)/ [pɾe.va.leˈse(h)]
  • (Brazil) IPA(key): /pɾe.va.leˈse(ʁ)/ [pɾe.va.leˈse(h)]
    • (São Paulo) IPA(key): /pɾe.va.leˈse(ɾ)/
    • (Rio de Janeiro) IPA(key): /pɾe.va.leˈse(ʁ)/ [pɾe.va.leˈse(χ)]
    • (Southern Brazil) IPA(key): /pɾe.va.leˈse(ɻ)/
 
  • (Portugal) IPA(key): /pɾɨ.vɐ.lɨˈseɾ/
  • (Portugal) IPA(key): /pɾɨ.vɐ.lɨˈseɾ/
    • (Northern Portugal) IPA(key): /pɾɨ.bɐ.lɨˈseɾ/ [pɾɨ.βɐ.lɨˈseɾ]
    • (Southern Portugal) IPA(key): /pɾɨ.vɐ.lɨˈse.ɾi/

  • Hyphenation: pre‧va‧le‧cer

Verb

[edit]

prevalecer (first-person singular present prevaleço, first-person singular preterite prevaleci, past participle prevalecido)

  1. to prevail
  2. to predominate

Spanish

[edit]

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /pɾebaleˈθeɾ/ [pɾe.β̞a.leˈθeɾ] (Spain)
  • IPA(key): /pɾebaleˈseɾ/ [pɾe.β̞a.leˈseɾ] (Latin America, Philippines)
  • Rhymes: -eɾ
  • Syllabification: pre‧va‧le‧cer

Verb

[edit]

prevalecer (first-person singular present prevalezco, first-person singular preterite prevalecí, past participle prevalecido)

  1. (intransitive) to prevail
